cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with optimizing U-Net-like encoder-decoder architectures for disparity estimation. Additionally, the use of gradient-based neural architecture search and Bayesian optimization for hyperparameter search suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The optimization techniques used in this work may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the application of the optimized architecture to disparity estimation suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
